org.apache.hadoop.hive.registry.impl

Class ZkRegistryBase<InstanceType extends ServiceInstance>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.hive.registry.impl.ZkRegistryBase<InstanceType>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    HS2ActivePassiveHARegistry, LlapZookeeperRegistryImpl, TezAmRegistryImpl

    public abstract class ZkRegistryBase<InstanceType extends ServiceInstance>
extends Object
    This is currently used for implementation inheritance only; it doesn't provide a unified flow into which one can just plug a few abstract method implementations, because providing one with getInstance method is a huge pain involving lots of generics. Also, different registries may have slightly different usage patterns anyway and noone would use a registry without knowing what type it is. So, it's mostly a grab bag of methods used by ServiceInstanceSet and other parts of each implementation.

                      String workerGroup,
                      String zkSaslLoginContextName,
                      String zkPrincipal,
                      String zkKeytab,
                      HiveConf.ConfVars aclsConfig)
        Parameters:
        rootNs - A single root namespace override. Not recommended.
        nsPrefix - The namespace prefix to use with default namespaces (appends 'sasl' for secure else 'unsecure' to namespace prefix to get effective root namespace).
        userScopePathPrefix - The prefix to use for the user-specific part of the path.
        workerPrefix - The prefix to use for each worker znode.
        workerGroup - group name to use for all workers
        zkSaslLoginContextName - SASL login context name for ZK security; null if not needed.
        zkPrincipal - ZK security principal.
        zkKeytab - ZK security keytab.
        aclsConfig - A config setting to use to determine if ACLs should be verified.
